        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 8 at 2:54AM CDT until June 8 at 3:45AM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>SVRAMA

The National Weather Service in Amarillo has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southern Armstrong County in the Panhandle of Texas...
Southeastern Randall County in the Panhandle of Texas...
West central Donley County in the Panhandle of Texas...

* Until 345 AM CDT.

* At 254 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 4 miles northwest
of Wayside, or 20 miles southeast of Canyon, moving southeast at 55
mph.

HAZARD...Two inch hail and 70 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect some tree damage. Damage is likely to mobile
homes, roofs, and outbuildings. People and animals
outdoors will be injured. Expect hail damage to roofs,
siding, windows, and vehicles.

* Locations impacted include...
Wayside and Palo Duro Canyon.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
